overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, aiming to validate its adherence to the provided Statement of
  Work and detailed functional specifications. The agent systematically analyzed
  the existing codebase, identified several critical gaps, and then proceeded to
  implement a series of enhancements. Key additions included a dynamic 1-10
  tiredness severity scale with urgent safety warnings, sophisticated detection
  logic for complex sleep disorders like COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome,
  and the integration of external resource links within the generated reports.
  Furthermore, the agent refined the Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS) scoring
  with weighted criteria, significantly expanded the CSV data export to capture
  all questionnaire responses, and introduced new questions for pain and chronic
  fatigue screening, complete with an alert for potential chronic fatigue
  syndrome. The implementation involved extensive modifications across types,
  validations, UI components, and report generation logic, ensuring a more
  robust and clinically relevant questionnaire.
